<p>I have a table bookorder_t with columns as follows orderid,bookid, ordersuccess . I want to find the all bookids where ordersuccess= 1, and count of book ids.</p>  <p>Suppose this is my bookorder_t</p>  <pre><code>orderid bookid  ordersuccess ---------------------------- 100      1         1 101      1         null 102      1         1 103      2         1 104      2         1 106      1         1 </code></pre>  <p>My expected result is</p>  <pre><code>bookid count 1       3 2       2 </code></pre>  <p>How to write query for this in in linq?</p>